AB  - Adiabatic quantum-flux-parametron (AQFP) is a new superconducting technology developed in recent years. It achieves the highest energy efficiency among the superconducting logic families and has excellent potential for implementing large-scale systems. Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) is one of the representative algorithms of deep learning and has been widely used in many fields, such as computer vision, in recent years. Thus, with the development of neural networks, AQFP will have a broad application prospect in high-performance computing and deep learning. In this study, we propose an AQFP-based processing unit for convolutional computation in CNN. We generate a circuit of the proposed processing unit using AQFP integrated circuit design methodology that contains logic synthesis, placement and routing, simulation and verification. The designed circuit is fabricated by the AIST 10kA/cm2 high-speed standard process (HSTP).
