AB  - The proceedings contain 25 papers. The topics discussed include: decision support information system for hardly diagnosing diseases; methodology of searching for all shortest routes in NoC; RedSib: a Smart-M3 semantic information broker implementation; Linux kernel drivers for I2C-manageable high precision power source based on ISL22317 and PCA9536 chips; Ubihomeserver front-end to the ubiquitous home environment; smartSlog Session Scheme for Smart-M3 applications; obtaining an SDL entity identifier using SDL/SystemC co-modeling; sensors in a smart room: preliminary study; load balancing routing algorithm for data gathering sensor network; the cross-platform application for arrhythmia detection; comparative analysis of indoor positioning systems based on communications supported by smartphones; research of MEMS accelerometers features in mobile phone; doctor search service. using Geo2tag LBS platform for mobile healthcare applications; realistic urban traffic simulation as vehicular ad-hoc network (VANET) via Veins framework; experience in developing reference applications with Qt/QML; Photovoltaic (PV) energy as recharge source for portable devices such as mobile phones; and analysis of discontinuous reception based energy-saving techniques.
