AB  - We present a quantum optimization algorithm for asymmetric traveling salesman problems. Simulations with a class of random problems show the algorithm concentrates amplitudes into short-length tours, on average. The probability to find the optimal tour with a fixed number of steps decreases exponentially, but is much better than random selection.
